properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 12 at 9:59PM CST until January 13 at 8:00AM CST by NWS Topeka KS
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibilities down to one quarter of a mile or less in
dense freezing fog.

* WHERE...Jefferson, Shawnee and Douglas Counties.

* WHEN...Fog is gradually developing as clouds clear from
southwest to northeast. As the clouds clear tonight, fog should
follow shortly. The fog should persist until after sunrise.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility and
slick roadways, bridges, and sidewalks.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you. Please be cautious as road conditions may
change very quickly and catch drivers off guard.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 8 AM CST MONDAY
